results.name: Number of prime factors of n apart from 2 or 3, counted with multiplicity.
comment: Self-similar in every second and in every third term, i.e. a(n)=a(2n)=a(3n). Logarithmic since a(b*c)=a(b)+a(c). Coincidentally, a(n)=A101040(n+78) for 1<n<20.
link: Reinhard Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
results.author: _Henry Bottomley_, May 17 2005
